      • processEvents

        void processEvents​(List<jetbrains.mps.smodel.event.SModelEvent> events)
        Invalidates internal state for editors affected by events. Called outside a read/write action and implementors are discouraged from starting their own read/write action to do any model traversals because events are delivered asynchronously in batches and the current model state may not correspond to the events.
        Parameters:
        events - events that occurred since the last call to this method (or since this instance was added to the highlighter)

      • update

        @NotNull
UpdateResult update​(EditorComponent editorComponent,
                    boolean incremental,
                    boolean applyQuickFixes,
                    jetbrains.mps.util.Cancellable cancellable)
        Checks editorComponent for messages. Should watch cancellable for cancellation.
        Parameters:
        editorComponent - the component to check
        incremental - if true, cached information may be used; if false, cached information should be forgotten and the editor component rechecked completely.
        applyQuickFixes - if true, the checker may apply any quick fixes.
        cancellable - an object to check periodically for cancellation requests (see Cancellable.isCancelled().
        Returns:
        an UpdateResult indicating whether the update completed successfully and possibly containing check results.

      • doneUpdating

        void doneUpdating()
        Invoked after calling update(jetbrains.mps.nodeEditor.EditorComponent, boolean, boolean, jetbrains.mps.util.Cancellable) on all needed editor components. Checkers that maintain one global "dirty" flag can mark themselves clean in this method.
